<HL>
   Norway's Unemployment Falls
</HL>
<DATE>
04/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B3C
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   OSLO -- Norway's unemployment rate fell to 4.2% in April
from 4.4% in March, but was up from 3.7% a year earlier, said
Arbeidsdirektoratet, the government's labor agency.
   Norway's jobless rate peaked at 4.7% in January, when
101,900 people were out of work.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The April total was 91,500, down 2,300 from March but up
11,700 from a year earlier. Of the total, 59,000 were men and
32,500 women.
   Not included in the official jobless rate were 50,200
people employed in extraordinary state work programs, down
4,100 from March, but up 11,200 from 12 months earlier.
