<LP>
   E-SYSTEMS Inc. (Dallas) -- Terry W. Heil, senior vice
president of E-Systems' information systems group, was named
senior vice president of the company. In his new position,
Mr. Heil will share responsibility for all the operational
units of this maker of defense electronic systems with
E-Systems' president and chief operating officer, Lowell
Lawson. Formerly, operations were supervised by two group
vice presidents and the president, but in a reorganization
the group vice president positions will be eliminated.
Charles R. Farmer Jr., senior vice president of the company's
electronic systems group, has announced he intends to retire
June 8.
