<HL>
   Business Brief -- Akzo N.V.:
   Company Posts 11% Drop
   In First-Quarter Earnings
</HL>
<DATE>
04/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   AKZOY
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Hurt by narrower profit margins, Dutch chemical giant Akzo
N.V. reported that first-quarter net income fell 11% from a
year earlier.
   Akzo recorded profit of 201.7 million guilders ($106.8
million) compared with the year-earlier 227.4 million
guilders even though sales rose 1.8%. Sales by the chemical
group rose to 4.58 billion guilders from 4.5 billion
guilders.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Akzo said pretax operating profit fell to 8.2% of sales
compared with 9.1% a year earlier. The chemical group's
pretax operating profit fell to 375.2 million guilders from
410.4 million guilders.
   As with net profit, per-share earnings also declined 11%
to 4.66 guilders from the 5.25 guilders.
</TEXT>
