bonds due June 5, 1992, priced at 101.85 to yield 13.69% less
full fees via lead manager Scotia McLeod. Fees 1 1/8.
   Deutsche Bank Finance N.V. Curacao (West German parent) --
100 million Swiss francs of 7 1/2% public bonds due May 16,
1995, priced at 101 1/4 via Deutsche Bank Suisse. Guaranteed
by Deutsche Bank AG.
   Export-Import Bank of Korea (Korea) -- 105 million
European currency units of 11% bonds due May 11, 1995, priced
at 101 5/8 via lead manager Merrill Lynch International Ltd.
The bonds are callable and puttable in May 1993 at par.
</TEXT>
